I troubel you again with a letter for Uranie. as I had one from her in-
cluding one from America. Here it is very cold. can you bear it well?

We are all pretty well thank God. The children are already full of joy
about Christmas, and we olld peopel like when it is over, however I have
not much troubel about it as dear Marie who likes to bake and make goodle
does all for me.

                              Adieu dear son
